security.AnalysisPrompt:
As {agentPersona}, analyze the following code for security vulnerabilities.

Code to analyze:
{code}

Compliance standards: {complianceStandards}
Business context: {businessContext}

Respond ONLY with valid JSON in this exact structure (no markdown, no explanation):
{
  "findings": [
    {
      "category": "SQL Injection" | "Hardcoded Credentials" | "Weak Encryption" | "Authentication" | "Authorization" | "Data Exposure",
      "description": "Detailed description of the vulnerability",
      "severity": "CRITICAL" | "HIGH" | "MEDIUM" | "LOW",
      "location": "Specific file, class, method, or line number",
      "evidence": ["Exact code snippet showing the issue"]
    }
  ],
  "recommendations": [
    {
      "title": "Short actionable title",
      "description": "What needs to be done",
      "implementation": "How to implement the fix",
      "priority": "CRITICAL" | "HIGH" | "MEDIUM" | "LOW",
      "estimatedHours": <number: estimate hours to implement based on complexity>
    }
  ],
  "businessImpact": "Business-focused explanation of security risks and compliance impact",
  "confidenceScore": <number 0-100: your confidence in this analysis>
}

IMPORTANT:
- Analyze the ACTUAL code provided above
- Calculate estimatedHours based on complexity: Simple fixes (4-8h), Moderate (8-24h), Complex (24-80h)
- Set confidenceScore based on code clarity and analysis certainty (60-100)
- Be specific about vulnerabilities found
- Include method/class names in location field
- Evidence should be actual code snippets from input
- Return ONLY the JSON, no other text

